.false.                                             ! debug_mode [true|false].                  Enables debug mode. Default: false
.false.                                             ! log_sync [true|false].                    Enables logging of MPI syncs in debug mode. Default: false

!!!**** PETSc control 
none                                                ! pestc_sort_mode:                          Configures PETSc matrix sortingo mode. none => no sort, ND => Nested Dissection,1WD => One-way Dissection,RCM => Reverse Cuthill-McKee,QMD => Quotient Minimum Degree
.false.                                             ! petsc_print_matrix [true|false]:          generate PETSc matrix image
.false.                                             ! petsc_debug_mode [true|false]:            write PETSc debug data on proc_*.log files
8  9                                                ! petsc_load_treshold_(min/max):            load treshold (in thousands) allowed per process for PETSc matrices 

!!!**** Multigrid Load treshold
4                                                   ! min_load_treshold:                        minimum load (ncell size in thousands) allowed per process for multigrid
10                                                  ! max_load_treshold:                        maximum load (ncell size in thousands) allowed per process for multigrid
.true.                                              ! min_treshold_only [true|false]:           consider only mininum treshold 

!!!**** Error subsystem control 
.true.                                              ! mfsim_override [true|false]:              allows override for non critical errors
1d3                                                 ! maxu_threshold:                           if maxU is above specified threshold, generate a critical error and shutdown MFSim
1d3                                                 ! maxv_threshold:                           if maxV is above specified threshold, generate a critical error and shutdown MFSim
1d3                                                 ! maxw_threshold:                           if maxW is above specified threshold, generate a critical error and shutdown MFSim
